You will be the first one to find out when my new ebook all about Instagram growth and monetization launches 🚀 next week. 

I will be giving you every strategy I used to go from 0 to 720k followers in 26 months and turned my Instagram account into a 6 figure business. 

Don't wait! Join the waitlist for special bonuses.

Paula

(Swipe 👈🏼)Influencers are those users who are identified as having influence, expertise or leadership within a particular niche or industry. So how do you become an influencer?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
👇 [Tag someone who think should try this!!!] 👇
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🤳 Choose your platform - Will it be Instagram? LinkedIn? TikTok? Think about your target audience and make sure you’re using the platform they use.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🤳 Create great (consistent!) content - Your content needs to be high quality, delivered consistently and keeping your audience engaged. Not just beautiful images - though that’s a given - make your captions engaging!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🤳 Use the algorithm - Know how Instagram works and use it. That means using hashtags the right way, posting at the right time (when your followers are online and engaging!) posting consistently and lastly providing value in every piece of content. 
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🤳 Engage the community - Social media is social, right? That means engagement! Be a peer IN the community and make sure you’re responding to comments and questions (as much as you can… it may be harder if you have hundreds of thousands of followers!). And don’t just engage on your own account - like and comment on other people’s posts within your industry or niche.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
🤳 Be authentic - People value authenticity over just about anything else on social media - they want meaningful, valuable content, not ‘fake’. Be your authentic, unique and memorable self!

node.text:
Delete, block, next.....remove toxic people from your life. Tag a friend that needs a reminder. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
You cannot hang with negative people and expect to live a positive life. 😮🤓⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Let go of the negative people in your life who are holding you back and weighing you down including close friends and family. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
People we need to leave behind. 👇🏼⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
1. The Debbie Downer⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Toxic people have a way of sucking the joy out of your good news and contorting your positive news into something negative. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
2. The Gaslighter⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Gaslighting is a psychological term that refers to one partner’s efforts to undermine the other’s grasp on reality in order to gain control. This is done by systematically making the victim feel like whatever the circumstances, her (or his) version of events is skewed, misconstrued, or imagined.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
3. The User⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
A user demands your time, energy and resources without taking your own wants and needs into consideration.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
4. The Friend You’ve Outgrown⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Friendships should be reciprocal and balanced. If they’re not, it may be time to move on.  Not everyone is meant to stay in your life.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
5.  The Critic⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Overly critical people often have low self-esteem and may be projecting their own insecurities onto the people around them.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
 So if a negative person is subtracting more than adding to your life, then make moves to distance yourself.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Hope this was helpful. Please share with a friend that needs a reminder. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Breath, Believe, Achieve ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
